{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Come and kiss me goodbye ere you leave [D7]me
Come and sit by my side one more [G]time
Though your love may belong to [D7]another
In my heart you'll always be [G]mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Here's your [C]ring on my hand just a plain golden [G]band
May I [D7]keep it as a token of our [G]love
And as years [C]come and go till my hair's white as [G]snow
I'll be [D7]true to the one that I [G]love
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
You may leave me behind here [D7]forever
You may lay me beneath the cold [G]clay
Just remember little darling you'll [D7]never
Find a friend like you're leaving here [G]today
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
